WEBVTT

﻿1
00:00:01.830 --> 00:00:04.231
(BIRD CHIRPING. VEHICLE APPROACHES)

2
00:00:04.242 --> 00:00:06.220
(BRAKES SQUEAL)

3
00:00:09.234 --> 00:00:11.267
- (ENGINE SHUTS OFF. KEYS JINGLE)
- (SIGHS)

4
00:00:13.000 --> 00:00:19.074
Watch Online Movies and Series for FREE
www.osdb.link/lm

5
00:00:31.022 --> 00:00:32.431
(CAR DOOR CLOSES)

6
00:00:37.016 --> 00:00:38.283
(KNOCK ON DOOR)

7
00:00:38.763 --> 00:00:41.655
Mrs. Landry. you're
looking lovely as ever.

8
00:00:41.666 --> 00:00:43.616
Jimmy McGill!

9
00:00:43.627 --> 00:00:45.592
W-What are you doing here?

10
00:00:45.603 --> 00:00:47.553
Oh. I was in the area. and I thought...

11
00:00:47.564 --> 00:00:50.431
I wonder how my favorite
former client is doing?

12
00:00:50.442 --> 00:00:51.939
And I have cookies.

13
00:00:51.963 --> 00:00:53.496
(CHUCKLING) Oh. you're so sweet.

14
00:00:53.498 --> 00:00:54.930
Come on in!

15
00:00:54.932 --> 00:00:56.041
Jimmy: After I made these.

16
00:00:56.052 --> 00:00:58.667
I looked down. and I thought. "Wow!

17
00:00:58.669 --> 00:01:00.990
That looks just like your Felix."

18
00:01:01.001 --> 00:01:02.056
(CHUCKLES)

19
00:01:02.067 --> 00:01:03.857
They do!

20
00:01:03.868 --> 00:01:05.978
You're so thoughtful.

21
00:01:05.989 --> 00:01:07.710
I was afraid you wouldn't be here.

22
00:01:07.712 --> 00:01:08.884
Thought. with that settlement money.

23
00:01:08.895 --> 00:01:11.647
you might've moved somewhere swankier.

24
00:01:11.649 --> 00:01:14.576
- What do you mean?
- The settlement.

25
00:01:14.587 --> 00:01:16.553
The Sandpiper case?

26
00:01:16.564 --> 00:01:18.120
Now. that's gotta be
wrapped up by now. right?

27
00:01:18.122 --> 00:01:22.396
Oh. that? That... that...
that... that's still years away.

28
00:01:22.407 --> 00:01:23.459
You haven't settled yet?

29
00:01:23.461 --> 00:01:26.128
No. I don't know all the
details yet. but Erin...

30
00:01:26.130 --> 00:01:29.965
uh. Erin Brill of Davis
& Main... do you know her?

31
00:01:29.976 --> 00:01:34.728
Lovely girl. (CHUCKLING) She
reminds me of a young Mary Martin.

32
00:01:34.739 --> 00:01:37.248
Oh. yes. I-I have met her.

33
00:01:37.259 --> 00:01:40.134
It's a... She's a
wonderful young lady. Uh...

34
00:01:40.145 --> 00:01:41.708
Well. she takes care of all of that.

35
00:01:41.719 --> 00:01:44.814
and she said there's
still a long way to go.

36
00:01:44.816 --> 00:01:47.513
But you've... received an offer. right?

37
00:01:47.524 --> 00:01:50.354
Something sent to you in writing?

38
00:01:50.365 --> 00:01:53.255
I mean. something more than
just Erin and you chatting?

39
00:01:53.257 --> 00:01:54.607
Oh.

40
00:01:57.958 --> 00:02:01.057
It's probably all here in this box.

41
00:02:01.068 --> 00:02:03.566
I can't make heads or tails of it.

42
00:02:03.568 --> 00:02:06.151
but you are welcome to look.

43
00:02:06.162 --> 00:02:07.561
You sure?

44
00:02:07.572 --> 00:02:10.002
(CHUCKLING) Of course. It's you.

45
00:02:11.627 --> 00:02:15.132
Well. uh. I gotta say...

46
00:02:15.143 --> 00:02:18.781
I can't blame you for getting
mixed up with all this.

47
00:02:18.783 --> 00:02:20.257
(CHUCKLES)

48
00:02:20.268 --> 00:02:21.900
I mean. these legal notices...

49
00:02:21.911 --> 00:02:25.087
I mean. no one really understands them.

50
00:02:25.089 --> 00:02:27.923
You know. (CHUCKLES)
I've got a law degree.

51
00:02:27.925 --> 00:02:30.259
And sometimes I can't even. uh...

52
00:02:34.037 --> 00:02:36.060
I can't even. uh...

53
00:02:37.658 --> 00:02:39.058
(SIGHS DEEPLY)

54
00:02:39.069 --> 00:02:40.970
(PAPER RUSTLES)

55
00:02:41.865 --> 00:02:43.739
You haven't. uh...

56
00:02:44.318 --> 00:02:45.975
accepted this?

57
00:02:45.977 --> 00:02:48.248
Erin says we should wait.

58
00:02:49.177 --> 00:02:50.412
But...

59
00:02:50.414 --> 00:02:52.076
(CHUCKLES)

60
00:02:52.420 --> 00:02:54.802
Erin doesn't really matter. does she?

61
00:02:54.813 --> 00:02:57.896
I mean. you're the Class Representative.

62
00:02:58.389 --> 00:02:59.822
That's a big deal.

63
00:02:59.824 --> 00:03:02.758
That means you and you alone decide.

64
00:03:02.760 --> 00:03:05.388
You're... you are the legal stand-in

65
00:03:05.399 --> 00:03:07.730
for your friends and neighbors.

66
00:03:07.732 --> 00:03:09.949
I-I don't know about all that. Jimmy.

67
00:03:09.960 --> 00:03:13.250
I-I just leave it all
to the professionals.

68
00:03:13.261 --> 00:03:15.047
Yeah. sure. sure.

69
00:03:15.058 --> 00:03:17.003
Lawyers know best. but...

70
00:03:17.691 --> 00:03:19.642
(CHUCKLING) I'm sorry.

71
00:03:19.644 --> 00:03:20.976
If you won the lottery.

72
00:03:20.978 --> 00:03:22.845
I mean. you'd take the lump sum. right?

73
00:03:22.847 --> 00:03:25.514
I mean. money now is
better than money later.

74
00:03:25.516 --> 00:03:28.174
- Bird in the hand!
- I suppose.

75
00:03:28.185 --> 00:03:30.252
The more time to enjoy it!

76
00:03:30.254 --> 00:03:31.687
(CHUCKLES)

77
00:03:31.689 --> 00:03:33.923
You really should talk to Erin.

78
00:03:33.925 --> 00:03:36.158
She knows all the ins and outs.

79
00:03:36.160 --> 00:03:37.826
(SIGHS) Ins and outs.

80
00:03:37.828 --> 00:03:40.941
Yeah. Erin sure knows those. (CHUCKLES)

81
00:03:40.952 --> 00:03:44.735
I'll be happy to talk to Erin. uh...

82
00:03:44.746 --> 00:03:46.635
Just... I just can't help but wonder

83
00:03:46.637 --> 00:03:50.449
- if she's taking every aspect into a...
- (KNOCK ON DOOR)

84
00:03:50.877 --> 00:03:52.492
Oh. Jimmy.

85
00:03:52.503 --> 00:03:54.547
I completely forgot...

86
00:03:54.558 --> 00:03:56.979
I'm on my way to chair yoga.

87
00:03:56.981 --> 00:03:58.314
I'm so sorry.

88
00:03:58.316 --> 00:03:59.682
No. it's okay.

89
00:03:59.684 --> 00:04:02.484
Um. I probably should be going.

90
00:04:02.486 --> 00:04:04.860
I have a lot to do.

91
00:04:04.871 --> 00:04:07.656
(INDISTINCT CONVERSATION IN DISTANCE)

92
00:04:08.792 --> 00:04:09.985
- (CHUCKLING)
- Hi.

93
00:04:09.996 --> 00:04:11.047
- Jimmy!
- Jimmy!

94
00:04:11.058 --> 00:04:13.977
- Jimmy!
- Rose. Myrtle. Helen.

95
00:04:14.362 --> 00:04:16.893
That chair yoga really works. huh?

96
00:04:16.909 --> 00:04:18.074
You all look 10 years younger.

97
00:04:18.085 --> 00:04:19.167
- Oh!
- (ALL CHUCKLING)

98
00:04:19.178 --> 00:04:20.970
- You honeydripper.
- Hey. hurry up.

99
00:04:20.972 --> 00:04:22.204
It starts in five minutes.

100
00:04:22.206 --> 00:04:23.292
Do you want to come with us?

101
00:04:23.303 --> 00:04:25.174
You're welcome to. We can have guests.

102
00:04:25.176 --> 00:04:28.644
I would love to. uh. but
I'm not dressed for it.

103
00:04:28.646 --> 00:04:31.148
So I'll take a rain check.

104
00:04:31.159 --> 00:04:32.265
Certainly.

105
00:04:32.276 --> 00:04:33.627
Thanks for the cookies. Jimmy.

106
00:04:33.638 --> 00:04:35.651
- Bye. Jimmy! Good to see ya.
- Bye!

107
00:04:35.662 --> 00:04:39.030
(VEHICLE PASSING)

108
00:04:40.324 --> 00:04:41.824
That can't be right.

109
00:04:41.826 --> 00:04:43.692
(CHUCKLING) Can't be right.

110
00:04:43.694 --> 00:04:44.960
(SIGHS)

111
00:04:47.906 --> 00:04:51.164
17.4 total.

112
00:04:51.789 --> 00:04:53.625
33% is the common fund.

113
00:04:53.636 --> 00:04:56.860
So. on 1/15.

114
00:04:56.871 --> 00:04:59.344
15 into 17...

115
00:05:00.610 --> 00:05:02.469
carry the 2.

116
00:05:03.117 --> 00:05:05.852
One million. one hundred and sixty...

117
00:05:07.438 --> 00:05:12.594
One million. one hundred and
sixty thousand! (CHUCKLING)

118
00:05:12.957 --> 00:05:14.133
(CHUCKLES)

119
00:05:14.144 --> 00:05:15.824
Holy shit!

120
00:05:33.119 --> 00:05:35.287
(INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS IN DISTANCE)

121
00:05:35.298 --> 00:05:36.539
(TELEPHONE RINGS IN DISTANCE)

122
00:05:36.586 --> 00:05:38.453
(ELEVATOR BELL DINGS)

123
00:05:39.877 --> 00:05:43.245
(MOTOR WHIRRING)

124
00:05:51.626 --> 00:05:53.359
- Mr. Ehrmantraut?
- Yeah.

125
00:05:53.361 --> 00:05:54.519
Sorry to keep you waiting.

126
00:05:54.530 --> 00:05:56.793
- It'll be right this way.
- (GRUNTS)

127
00:05:57.144 --> 00:05:59.798
Can I get you anything to
drink? Tea. water. espresso?

128
00:05:59.800 --> 00:06:01.808
No. I'm fine. Thank you.

129
00:06:02.481 --> 00:06:05.738
(INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS.
TELEPHONE RINGING)

130
00:06:15.719 --> 00:06:17.298
(KNOCKS ON DOOR)

131
00:06:18.158 --> 00:06:19.451
Ms. Rodarte Quayle?

132
00:06:19.453 --> 00:06:21.455
- I have your next...
- Yes. thank you.

133
00:06:21.466 --> 00:06:23.681
Mr. Ehrmantraut. Lydia Rodarte-Quayle.

134
00:06:23.692 --> 00:06:26.431
- Mike.
- Thanks. Justin.

135
00:06:26.442 --> 00:06:30.283
Have a seat. um... Mike.

136
00:06:30.791 --> 00:06:32.548
HR sent up your start paperwork.

137
00:06:32.559 --> 00:06:35.260
I-9. W-2. Pretty standard.

138
00:06:37.471 --> 00:06:40.973
Could I have your driver's
license and Social Security card?

139
00:06:40.975 --> 00:06:42.126
Why?

140
00:06:42.137 --> 00:06:44.188
My assistant needs to make a copy.

141
00:06:45.173 --> 00:06:49.138
How does this "hire" work.
exactly? Walk me through it.

142
00:06:49.149 --> 00:06:51.083
You'll receive a paycheck from Madrigal

143
00:06:51.085 --> 00:06:53.085
in the amount of $10.000 per week.

144
00:06:53.087 --> 00:06:54.438
I believe at that rate.

145
00:06:54.449 --> 00:06:57.735
your "employment" should be
paid out in about 20 weeks.

146
00:06:57.746 --> 00:07:01.490
Mr. Fring has arranged to
cover FICA. Social Security...

147
00:07:01.501 --> 00:07:03.648
the entirety of the tax burden.

148
00:07:03.659 --> 00:07:05.960
I assume that's all right with you?

149
00:07:08.282 --> 00:07:09.735
Good. So. to that end.

150
00:07:09.737 --> 00:07:12.314
I have you down as a
"logistics consultant."

151
00:07:12.325 --> 00:07:14.060
What is that?

152
00:07:14.071 --> 00:07:17.591
It's a person who consults on logistics.

153
00:07:17.602 --> 00:07:19.196
Does it matter?

154
00:07:20.032 --> 00:07:22.915
I'm not long on logistics.

155
00:07:22.917 --> 00:07:24.790
"Security consultant" would be better.

156
00:07:24.801 --> 00:07:26.876
I used to be a cop.

157
00:07:26.887 --> 00:07:29.121
That will look better
on your "work history"

158
00:07:29.123 --> 00:07:31.517
than your current employer. SMQ Parking.

159
00:07:31.528 --> 00:07:34.353
So. you take my money.

160
00:07:34.364 --> 00:07:36.920
you run it through this
joint. and it comes out clean.

161
00:07:36.931 --> 00:07:38.564
- That it?
- Yes.

162
00:07:39.204 --> 00:07:41.204
Who knows this operation?

163
00:07:41.215 --> 00:07:43.360
You... anyone else?

164
00:07:43.371 --> 00:07:45.626
- No.
- You sure?

165
00:07:46.720 --> 00:07:50.609
May I ask. what precisely
is your concern here?

166
00:07:50.611 --> 00:07:52.392
I am concerned about what happens

167
00:07:52.403 --> 00:07:55.581
if you put my real name in your books.

168
00:07:56.048 --> 00:07:58.734
Your Madrigal is a German company.

169
00:07:58.745 --> 00:08:02.280
One thing I know about Germans
is they love a good audit.

170
00:08:04.048 --> 00:08:07.564
I oversee eight freight terminals
across Texas and the Southwest.

171
00:08:07.575 --> 00:08:10.514
Operating costs range between $800.000

172
00:08:10.525 --> 00:08:13.089
and a million dollars per week.

173
00:08:13.100 --> 00:08:16.779
All due respect. Mike. but your money?

174
00:08:16.790 --> 00:08:18.490
It's a rounding error.

175
00:08:18.501 --> 00:08:20.982
If the IRS or anyone else looks.

176
00:08:20.993 --> 00:08:22.939
you're a contractor for a
multinational corporation

177
00:08:22.950 --> 00:08:26.373
with 114.000 employees worldwide.

178
00:08:26.384 --> 00:08:28.814
You're like every other
person in this building.

179
00:08:28.816 --> 00:08:30.540
Like you?

180
00:08:31.985 --> 00:08:34.189
You think I'm not on the books?

181
00:08:34.200 --> 00:08:37.021
I am. Under my own name.

182
00:08:37.032 --> 00:08:39.992
- This the way you handled it before?
- Handled what?

183
00:08:39.994 --> 00:08:43.128
The money. For Fring's other guys.

184
00:08:43.973 --> 00:08:45.640
Other guys?

185
00:08:46.587 --> 00:08:49.104
This is the first time I've done this...

186
00:08:49.115 --> 00:08:50.415
for anyone.

187
00:08:51.751 --> 00:08:54.357
I don't know what you do. but...

188
00:08:54.368 --> 00:08:57.376
Mr. Fring must think
you're quite good at it.

189
00:08:57.378 --> 00:08:59.368
(SIGHS)

190
00:09:13.017 --> 00:09:14.693
20 weeks?

191
00:09:14.695 --> 00:09:16.628
The sooner you're off
my books. the better.

192
00:09:16.630 --> 00:09:18.212
- (INTERCOM BEEPS)
- Justin?

193
00:09:25.859 --> 00:09:28.453
Can you make a copy of
these. please? Thank you.

194
00:09:30.726 --> 00:09:32.218
(DOOR CLOSES)

195
00:09:33.724 --> 00:09:35.171
What?

196
00:09:37.345 --> 00:09:39.750
This is a very nice office.

197
00:09:40.221 --> 00:09:41.695
Thank you.

198
00:09:44.859 --> 00:09:48.201
Seem to be risking a
lot for a drug dealer.

199
00:09:48.212 --> 00:09:49.825
"Drug dealer"?

200
00:09:52.500 --> 00:09:53.866
(SCOFFS)

201
00:09:53.868 --> 00:09:56.602
If that's all you think he is...

202
00:09:57.369 --> 00:09:59.942
then you don't know Gustavo Fring.

203
00:10:10.141 --> 00:10:11.953
(SIGHS)

204
00:10:15.890 --> 00:10:19.204
(PEN SCRATCHES)

205
00:10:19.215 --> 00:10:21.426
Howard: Let me understand you...

206
00:10:21.428 --> 00:10:23.517
you're proposing to double our premiums

207
00:10:23.528 --> 00:10:26.765
on every one of our
practicing attorneys?

208
00:10:27.408 --> 00:10:29.034
Man: We know this is abrupt...

209
00:10:29.036 --> 00:10:31.270
new issues have come to light.

210
00:10:31.272 --> 00:10:33.147
"New issues"?

211
00:10:33.158 --> 00:10:35.529
You mean Mr. McGill's
testimony at the Bar?

212
00:10:35.540 --> 00:10:37.075
That's a part of it. yes.

213
00:10:37.077 --> 00:10:39.365
After 25 years of paying full premiums.

214
00:10:39.376 --> 00:10:41.428
I can count on one hand
the number of our claims.

215
00:10:41.439 --> 00:10:43.443
Woman: This is an underwriting
decision... that's all.

216
00:10:43.454 --> 00:10:45.050
You shouldn't take it personally.

217
00:10:45.052 --> 00:10:46.752
Man: In some special circumstances.

218
00:10:46.754 --> 00:10:48.554
we have been known to extend a rider.

219
00:10:48.556 --> 00:10:49.788
What kind of rider?

220
00:10:49.790 --> 00:10:51.657
Woman: A senior.
management-level partner

221
00:10:51.659 --> 00:10:53.659
who would supervise Charles' work.

222
00:10:53.661 --> 00:10:56.274
attend court and client
meetings with him.

223
00:10:56.285 --> 00:10:57.585
review filings.

224
00:10:57.596 --> 00:10:58.729
Man: The few times we've done this.

225
00:10:58.740 --> 00:11:00.385
it's been for clients
with a high probability

226
00:11:00.396 --> 00:11:02.651
of catastrophic health
failure as a precaution.

227
00:11:02.662 --> 00:11:05.245
What you're saying is that
for any case Charles takes on.

228
00:11:05.256 --> 00:11:07.440
another partner would
be tied up. as well.

229
00:11:07.451 --> 00:11:08.851
and we don't bill a penny more?

230
00:11:08.862 --> 00:11:10.633
This is ludicrous.

231
00:11:10.644 --> 00:11:13.273
The insurance industry
is heavily regulated.

232
00:11:13.284 --> 00:11:14.831
I can think of a dozen infractions

233
00:11:14.842 --> 00:11:17.174
- right here off the top of my head.
- Mr. McGill...

234
00:11:17.183 --> 00:11:19.784
You're hoping we'll
either find another carrier

235
00:11:19.786 --> 00:11:21.617
or cut you an enormous check.

236
00:11:21.628 --> 00:11:22.828
Win-win for you!

237
00:11:22.839 --> 00:11:25.022
I assure you. neither
is going to happen.

238
00:11:25.024 --> 00:11:26.852
What will happen is very simple...

239
00:11:26.863 --> 00:11:28.414
you're going to do right by us

240
00:11:28.425 --> 00:11:30.160
or we will compel you to do so.

241
00:11:30.171 --> 00:11:32.763
- What do you mean by "compel"?
- You know exactly what I mean.

242
00:11:32.765 --> 00:11:35.633
If you're threatening litigation.
I'm afraid this meeting is over.

243
00:11:35.644 --> 00:11:37.254
Then it's over.

244
00:11:37.933 --> 00:11:39.581
Thank you for your time.

245
00:11:39.601 --> 00:11:42.152
Mr. Hamlin. Mr. McGill.

246
00:11:44.443 --> 00:11:46.207
(DOOR CREAKS)

247
00:11:52.285 --> 00:11:54.274
All right. Where do we begin?

248
00:11:54.285 --> 00:11:56.821
Francis should start
digging into regulations.

249
00:11:56.823 --> 00:11:59.457
I'm sorry I don't have the code sections

250
00:11:59.459 --> 00:12:00.891
at my fingertips just now.

251
00:12:00.893 --> 00:12:02.693
Let's pull a team of associates

252
00:12:02.695 --> 00:12:05.893
and get them looking at every
angle of injunctive relief.

253
00:12:05.904 --> 00:12:07.248
- Before close of business...
- (GLASS THUMPS LIGHTLY)

254
00:12:07.259 --> 00:12:09.633
We're going to hit Santa
Rosa with a demand letter

255
00:12:09.635 --> 00:12:11.402
that'll make their heads spin.

256
00:12:11.404 --> 00:12:13.471
(CHUCKLES) Odds are. inside a week.

257
00:12:13.473 --> 00:12:15.334
they'll be sitting at the table again.

258
00:12:15.345 --> 00:12:17.240
- (LIQUID POURING)
- And if not...

259
00:12:17.243 --> 00:12:20.009
well. we've never
shied away from a fight.

260
00:12:20.020 --> 00:12:21.453
(DECANTER THUMPS LIGHTLY)

261
00:12:23.870 --> 00:12:25.828
Chuck. do you remember Al McConnell?

262
00:12:25.839 --> 00:12:27.718
Of course. Helluva litigator.

263
00:12:27.720 --> 00:12:29.183
Retired now. isn't he?

264
00:12:29.194 --> 00:12:31.492
He's a professor at UNM now.

265
00:12:31.503 --> 00:12:34.492
Wrote a fantastic book on
SCOTUS during Reconstruction.

266
00:12:34.494 --> 00:12:35.726
Fascinating stuff.

267
00:12:35.728 --> 00:12:36.878
Okay...

268
00:12:36.889 --> 00:12:39.586
I was talking to him. and he mentioned

269
00:12:39.597 --> 00:12:42.539
he'd love you to come
speak to his One-Ls.

270
00:12:42.550 --> 00:12:45.620
Maybe make it a regular
thing. if you wanted.

271
00:12:45.749 --> 00:12:47.082
(SCOFFS)

272
00:12:47.093 --> 00:12:48.873
What are you talking about. Howard?

273
00:12:48.875 --> 00:12:51.047
What I'm saying is...

274
00:12:51.058 --> 00:12:53.911
maybe it's time to hang up your spurs.

275
00:12:54.433 --> 00:12:56.304
Become partner emeritus...

276
00:12:56.315 --> 00:12:58.883
leave your name on the firm
but focus on your legacy.

277
00:12:58.885 --> 00:13:02.320
You always said you wanted to
work on the Commerce Clause...

278
00:13:02.331 --> 00:13:04.031
you can write the book on it.

279
00:13:04.042 --> 00:13:06.876
And no longer be a practicing lawyer.

280
00:13:08.643 --> 00:13:11.297
Chuck. there's more to life than this.

281
00:13:11.308 --> 00:13:14.131
That day is far in the future. Howard.

282
00:13:14.133 --> 00:13:16.933
And I don't appreciate the suggestion.

283
00:13:18.698 --> 00:13:20.604
What if it's not a suggestion?

284
00:13:20.606 --> 00:13:21.784
Meaning? (GLASS THUMPS)

285
00:13:21.795 --> 00:13:24.708
Meaning. if enough people
tell you that you're drunk.

286
00:13:24.710 --> 00:13:26.977
maybe it's time to sit down.

287
00:13:29.614 --> 00:13:32.993
You want me to retire
over this... insurance?!

288
00:13:33.004 --> 00:13:34.434
It's not just the insurance.

289
00:13:34.445 --> 00:13:37.279
That's the straw that
broke the camel's back.

290
00:13:38.637 --> 00:13:41.325
So this is about my condition.

291
00:13:41.607 --> 00:13:42.989
Look!

292
00:13:43.662 --> 00:13:44.989
Look!

293
00:13:47.382 --> 00:13:49.027
You see?

294
00:13:50.028 --> 00:13:51.936
(CHUCKLING) See?

295
00:13:51.938 --> 00:13:53.504
I'm better!

296
00:13:53.942 --> 00:13:56.309
(CHUCKLING) Howard. I'm fine!

297
00:14:00.067 --> 00:14:02.572
This is not what "fine" looks like.

298
00:14:02.583 --> 00:14:04.231
(SIGHS)

299
00:14:04.778 --> 00:14:06.444
(LAMP THUDS)

300
00:14:06.455 --> 00:14:08.986
Chuck. you are the best
legal mind I've ever known.

301
00:14:08.988 --> 00:14:10.588
Hands down.

302
00:14:11.208 --> 00:14:13.670
But your decision-making has become...

303
00:14:13.681 --> 00:14:15.301
unpredictable.

304
00:14:16.195 --> 00:14:19.700
And I can't be partners with
someone whose judgment I don't trust.

305
00:14:24.500 --> 00:14:25.919
Chuck...

306
00:14:28.198 --> 00:14:32.280
(INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS)

307
00:14:32.291 --> 00:14:33.950
(DOOR CLOSES)

308
00:14:38.556 --> 00:14:42.334
This right here is the
Texas-New Mexico border.

309
00:14:42.344 --> 00:14:43.474
(GRUNTS)

310
00:14:43.486 --> 00:14:47.522
Now. all of my wells are square...

311
00:14:47.533 --> 00:14:49.529
on the Texas side.

312
00:14:49.539 --> 00:14:52.747
When I negotiated for the
mineral and property rights.

313
00:14:52.758 --> 00:14:56.966
the surveyors said that the
next nearest pool extended to...

314
00:15:01.015 --> 00:15:02.633
about here.

315
00:15:02.644 --> 00:15:04.090
Right.

316
00:15:04.101 --> 00:15:06.312
But... after some extraction.

317
00:15:06.324 --> 00:15:09.173
the west wall of the salt dome gave way.

318
00:15:09.184 --> 00:15:11.591
opening up another pool
that extends... what...

319
00:15:11.602 --> 00:15:13.250
100 yards over the border?

320
00:15:13.252 --> 00:15:14.774
That's about the size of it. yeah.

321
00:15:14.792 --> 00:15:17.560
And now you have New Mexico
rights holders to deal with.

322
00:15:18.063 --> 00:15:19.969
You know. they should get
profit on what's theirs.

323
00:15:19.980 --> 00:15:21.969
but now I've got two
states coming after me

324
00:15:21.979 --> 00:15:24.179
for taxes on each and every gallon.

325
00:15:25.553 --> 00:15:27.531
No equipment crosses the border?

326
00:15:27.542 --> 00:15:29.141
No. Ma'am.

327
00:15:29.159 --> 00:15:31.617
Nothing below the surface. like the...

328
00:15:32.703 --> 00:15:34.460
What... is it a drill bit?

329
00:15:34.462 --> 00:15:37.203
It would be the sucker rod at
this point. but no. none of that.

330
00:15:37.214 --> 00:15:38.998
Only on the Texas side.

331
00:15:39.000 --> 00:15:42.501
But that's not stopping New
Mexico from trying to bleed me.

332
00:15:42.861 --> 00:15:45.102
You said on the phone
you have a solution.

333
00:15:46.407 --> 00:15:48.805
You don't negotiate a lease
with the rights holders.

334
00:15:48.816 --> 00:15:51.385
- You offer to pay them damages.
- Damages?

335
00:15:51.396 --> 00:15:53.526
For diminishing their resource.

336
00:15:53.541 --> 00:15:57.136
A significant fraction of the
value of the New Mexico portion.

337
00:15:57.147 --> 00:15:59.354
but without paying for
the rights themselves.

338
00:15:59.754 --> 00:16:01.745
So a kind of a payoff.

339
00:16:02.955 --> 00:16:04.901
Then you don't get hit with the taxes.

340
00:16:04.912 --> 00:16:07.045
You think you can make that fly?

341
00:16:07.056 --> 00:16:09.557
If someone came to me with this offer...

342
00:16:09.568 --> 00:16:11.430
I'd sure as hell take it.

343
00:16:11.432 --> 00:16:13.899
(CHUCKLING) Wish I'd called you sooner.

344
00:16:14.471 --> 00:16:16.206
Way they're makin' noise.

345
00:16:16.217 --> 00:16:18.854
if I don't get this thing wrapped
up by the end of the quarter.

346
00:16:18.865 --> 00:16:22.147
I'm pretty sure the tax
boys are gonna take me apart.

347
00:16:22.158 --> 00:16:24.659
And that's two weeks from now?

348
00:16:27.088 --> 00:16:28.614
I can do it by then.

349
00:16:28.616 --> 00:16:30.182
Really?

350
00:16:30.184 --> 00:16:32.072
If we can get all the
rights holders in one place.

351
00:16:32.083 --> 00:16:34.617
I can walk them through
what we're proposing.

352
00:16:34.628 --> 00:16:36.789
If they're smart. they'll go for it.

353
00:16:36.791 --> 00:16:38.290
Well. hot damn.

354
00:16:40.936 --> 00:16:43.819
Kevin said you were a miracle
worker. but I didn't believe him.

355
00:16:43.830 --> 00:16:45.631
I'm startin' to.

356
00:16:45.633 --> 00:16:49.034
Yeah. well. let me work that miracle
first. then we'll talk. (CHUCKLES)

357
00:16:49.036 --> 00:16:50.469
You know the way outta here?

358
00:16:50.471 --> 00:16:53.850
I got a drill-head that's acting up on me

359
00:16:53.861 --> 00:16:56.408
out on the north forty I gotta check.

360
00:16:56.410 --> 00:16:57.876
Yeah. I'm good.

361
00:16:57.878 --> 00:16:59.241
You need anything from me.

362
00:16:59.252 --> 00:17:00.944
- you got my cell. Call me.
- (ENGINE STARTS)

363
00:17:00.955 --> 00:17:02.405
Will do.

364
00:17:05.192 --> 00:17:08.560
(MACHINERY CREAKING)

365
00:17:17.631 --> 00:17:19.765
(CAR DOOR CLOSES. ENGINE STARTS)

366
00:17:21.302 --> 00:17:22.960
(RECORDER CLICKS)

367
00:17:22.971 --> 00:17:26.103
Billy Gatwood meeting
notes. Contact Gatwood Oil.

368
00:17:26.114 --> 00:17:29.455
Get names and numbers for
New Mexico rights holders...

369
00:17:31.525 --> 00:17:34.056
(WHEELS GRINDING)

370
00:17:34.067 --> 00:17:35.564
Shit!

371
00:17:40.916 --> 00:17:42.583
(MACHINERY CREAKING)

372
00:18:22.878 --> 00:18:27.687
(CAR CREAKING)

373
00:18:35.342 --> 00:18:37.209
No. no. no. no!

374
00:18:37.211 --> 00:18:39.344
No. no. no! Shit!

375
00:18:41.315 --> 00:18:42.714
(BRAKES SQUEAL)

376
00:18:42.716 --> 00:18:44.047
(SIGHS)

377
00:18:47.316 --> 00:18:49.477
(MACHINERY CREAKING)

378
00:18:50.357 --> 00:18:53.251
(BREATHING DEEPLY)

379
00:18:57.531 --> 00:18:59.524
(SEAT BELT CLICKS)

380
00:18:59.535 --> 00:19:01.668
(ENGINE STARTS)

381
00:19:03.040 --> 00:19:04.138
(RECORDER CLICKS)

382
00:19:04.149 --> 00:19:07.201
Continuing notes from
Gatwood Oil meeting.

383
00:19:07.212 --> 00:19:09.454
Contact rights holders.

384
00:19:09.465 --> 00:19:11.454
- begin scheduling.
- (GEARSHIFT CLICKS)

385
00:19:14.508 --> 00:19:17.547
(MACHINERY CREAKING)

386
00:19:17.558 --> 00:19:20.102
- (LES MCCANN'S "MCCANNA" PLAYS)
- (TIRES SQUEAL)

387
00:19:28.874 --> 00:19:30.908
(ENGINE SHUTS OFF. MUSIC STOPS)

388
00:19:35.202 --> 00:19:36.635
Howard!

389
00:19:37.682 --> 00:19:38.993
(SIGHS)

390
00:19:39.004 --> 00:19:43.041
- What are you doing here. Jimmy?
- We have business to discuss.

391
00:19:43.043 --> 00:19:44.943
Is this about Chuck?

392
00:19:44.945 --> 00:19:46.745
Who?

393
00:19:46.747 --> 00:19:49.424
If you actually have business.
then call my secretary.

394
00:19:49.435 --> 00:19:52.150
I did. She stonewalled
me. as if you didn't know.

395
00:19:52.152 --> 00:19:53.608
Sandpiper.

396
00:19:53.619 --> 00:19:55.721
- What about it?
- It's time to settle.

397
00:19:55.723 --> 00:19:57.337
I-I saw the current offer.

398
00:19:57.348 --> 00:20:00.243
The clients make their losses
back. plus a solid chunk of change.

399
00:20:00.254 --> 00:20:01.407
(SIGHS)

400
00:20:01.418 --> 00:20:03.258
Not that it's any of your business.

401
00:20:03.269 --> 00:20:06.058
but we project a final number
far higher than the current offer.

402
00:20:06.069 --> 00:20:07.871
I get it. I get it. You hold out.

403
00:20:07.882 --> 00:20:10.269
maybe you squeeze a grand
more for each client.

404
00:20:10.280 --> 00:20:12.527
Meanwhile. HHM nets a few million.

405
00:20:12.551 --> 00:20:15.399
You know. you're screwing the
clients for your own benefit.

406
00:20:15.410 --> 00:20:18.410
Oh. so now you're
worried about the clients?

407
00:20:18.412 --> 00:20:20.027
It's the right thing
to do. and you know it.

408
00:20:20.038 --> 00:20:21.547
Please.

409
00:20:21.558 --> 00:20:24.416
All you care about is
your share of the payout.

410
00:20:24.418 --> 00:20:25.598
(CHUCKLES)

411
00:20:25.609 --> 00:20:27.683
It's like talking to Gollum.

412
00:20:27.694 --> 00:20:30.587
You're transparent. And pathetic.

413
00:20:30.598 --> 00:20:32.024
(BRIEFCASE THUMPS LIGHTLY)

414
00:20:32.026 --> 00:20:33.933
You want a handout?

415
00:20:35.394 --> 00:20:36.519
Here.

416
00:20:38.599 --> 00:20:39.824
Huh?

417
00:20:41.001 --> 00:20:42.805
Next time...

418
00:20:42.816 --> 00:20:44.636
why don't you bring a tin cup?

419
00:20:44.638 --> 00:20:46.551
It'd be more honest.

420
00:20:48.042 --> 00:20:50.642
Listen. Howard. settle
this and settle it now.

421
00:20:50.644 --> 00:20:52.410
It's in everyone's best interests!

422
00:20:52.421 --> 00:20:54.479
Meaning it's in your best interests.

423
00:20:54.481 --> 00:20:56.448
And if we don't. what are you gonna do?

424
00:20:56.450 --> 00:20:58.183
Peel off some members of the class.

425
00:20:58.185 --> 00:21:00.087
leak some insider info to Schweikart?

426
00:21:00.098 --> 00:21:02.287
Oh. I doubt it. I know you're low enough

427
00:21:02.289 --> 00:21:04.156
to do something like that.
but you're too damn greedy.

428
00:21:04.158 --> 00:21:05.398
- (ELEVATOR PLAYS MELODY)
- You do any of that.

429
00:21:05.409 --> 00:21:07.703
and you'll be jeopardizing your payday.

430
00:21:08.696 --> 00:21:10.845
You'll get your damn money.

431
00:21:10.856 --> 00:21:12.648
You're just gonna have to wait for it.

432
00:21:14.201 --> 00:21:16.735
(MACHINERY CREAKING)

433
00:21:16.737 --> 00:21:19.104
(LIGHTER CLICKING)

434
00:21:33.487 --> 00:21:37.065
(CLICKING CONTINUES)

435
00:21:48.060 --> 00:21:50.866
(CELLPHONE BUZZING)

436
00:21:56.510 --> 00:21:57.961
(CELLPHONE BEEPS)

437
00:22:51.660 --> 00:22:53.082
Don Hector...

438
00:23:05.530 --> 00:23:07.112
Don Hector?

439
00:23:07.114 --> 00:23:09.366
(GROANING)

440
00:23:22.024 --> 00:23:24.362
(PANTING)

441
00:23:30.504 --> 00:23:33.839
(PANTING CONTINUES)

442
00:24:02.072 --> 00:24:04.579
(BOZ SCAGGS' "LOWDOWN" PLAYS)

443
00:24:06.487 --> 00:24:10.354
(SQUEAKING)

444
00:24:11.834 --> 00:24:15.202
(MUSIC CONTINUES)

445
00:24:34.727 --> 00:24:38.566
(INDISTINCT CONVERSATION IN DISTANCE)

446
00:24:40.680 --> 00:24:42.297
Irene: Well. we go around about.

447
00:24:42.321 --> 00:24:44.860
you know. six times. I think.

448
00:24:44.890 --> 00:24:49.368
I think we're... Yeah.
I think... I think so.

449
00:24:50.391 --> 00:24:51.852
I know!

450
00:24:51.863 --> 00:24:53.663
This is so good for you.

451
00:24:53.665 --> 00:24:54.907
Hello. ladies.

452
00:24:54.918 --> 00:24:56.366
Good morning.

453
00:24:56.368 --> 00:24:57.801
- Hi! Jimmy!
- Hi. Jimmy.

454
00:24:57.803 --> 00:24:59.169
Jimmy!

455
00:24:59.171 --> 00:25:01.738
Oh. y-you... you girls
go on a little bit.

456
00:25:01.740 --> 00:25:03.649
I'll... I'll catch up with you.

457
00:25:03.660 --> 00:25:04.892
- Jimmy!
- (LAUGHS)

458
00:25:04.903 --> 00:25:06.188
Wow. Irene!

459
00:25:06.199 --> 00:25:08.478
Fancy running into
you twice in one week.

460
00:25:08.480 --> 00:25:09.913
How lucky am I?

461
00:25:09.915 --> 00:25:11.266
Y-You're a mall-walker?

462
00:25:11.277 --> 00:25:13.277
- I had no idea!
- Me?

463
00:25:13.288 --> 00:25:15.051
Oh. yeah. Big time.

464
00:25:15.053 --> 00:25:17.320
I mean. it's great for cardio.

465
00:25:17.322 --> 00:25:21.115
Hamstrings. glutes. I-T band.

466
00:25:21.126 --> 00:25:22.693
I'm a huge mall-walker.

467
00:25:22.704 --> 00:25:24.537
Been out of the game for awhile.

468
00:25:24.548 --> 00:25:26.396
Developed this damn plantar fasciitis.

469
00:25:26.398 --> 00:25:28.064
- Mnh. Mnh.
- Hurts like a bear.

470
00:25:28.066 --> 00:25:30.469
Oh. I'm so sorry to hear about that.

471
00:25:30.480 --> 00:25:32.347
(GRUNTS) Well. hey.

472
00:25:32.358 --> 00:25:34.337
I got the cure right here.

473
00:25:35.391 --> 00:25:36.706
Pow!

474
00:25:36.708 --> 00:25:40.377
These have a special
gel and resistance coils

475
00:25:40.379 --> 00:25:41.611
and buncha stuff.

476
00:25:41.613 --> 00:25:43.665
It's like walkin' on pillows.

477
00:25:43.676 --> 00:25:46.716
Well. they... they...
they look comfortable.

478
00:25:46.718 --> 00:25:48.118
You like 'em?

479
00:25:48.120 --> 00:25:51.388
Well. they... they're quite stylish.

480
00:25:51.390 --> 00:25:53.711
Hey. y'know what? (CHUCKLES)

481
00:25:53.722 --> 00:25:56.011
I bought a pair for my
girlfriend. and they don't fit her.

482
00:25:56.022 --> 00:25:58.128
And the store has this...
wouldn't you know it?

483
00:25:58.130 --> 00:26:00.296
- No-refunds policy.
- Oh.

484
00:26:00.298 --> 00:26:01.760
What size are you?

485
00:26:02.705 --> 00:26:05.526
7 1/2. 7 1/2.

486
00:26:05.552 --> 00:26:07.171
(INHALES SHARPLY)

487
00:26:07.182 --> 00:26:09.526
Oh. there we go.

488
00:26:10.208 --> 00:26:12.042
- (GRUNTS)
- (TRUNK CLOSES)

489
00:26:12.044 --> 00:26:15.779
(YOUNG-HOLT UNLIMITED'S
"SOULFUL STRUT" PLAYS)

490
00:26:17.115 --> 00:26:18.481
How does that feel?

491
00:26:18.483 --> 00:26:19.783
Oh!

492
00:26:21.029 --> 00:26:23.897
- Oh. I-I see what you mean. They...
- (CHUCKLES)

493
00:26:23.908 --> 00:26:28.218
They are so nice. and
they fit like a dream!

494
00:26:28.229 --> 00:26:31.061
But I-I can't take
these for free. Jimmy.

495
00:26:31.063 --> 00:26:32.726
Oh. please.

496
00:26:32.737 --> 00:26:35.274
There is one thing you could do for me?

497
00:26:35.285 --> 00:26:36.785
What's that?

498
00:26:37.104 --> 00:26:38.760
Don't tell the other
folks I gave 'em to ya.

499
00:26:38.771 --> 00:26:41.260
I don't want to look like
I'm playing favorites.

500
00:26:41.773 --> 00:26:44.433
- My lips are sealed.
- Then you go and enjoy those.

501
00:26:44.444 --> 00:26:45.738
I'm gonna go get my heart rate back up.

502
00:26:45.749 --> 00:26:47.488
- Oh. thank you!
- And I'll see you later.

503
00:26:47.506 --> 00:26:49.763
Thank you so much. Jimmy!

504
00:26:49.774 --> 00:26:51.179
(SIGHS)

505
00:26:51.230 --> 00:26:52.577
(SIGHS)

506
00:26:52.588 --> 00:26:54.688
(HERB ALPERT & THE TIJUANA
BRASS BAND'S "POPCORN" PLAYS)

507
00:26:57.277 --> 00:26:58.809
(SIGHS)

508
00:26:58.820 --> 00:27:00.918
Right hand. friends...
the hand of love.

509
00:27:01.285 --> 00:27:02.959
Now. watch. and I'll show
you the story of life.

510
00:27:02.961 --> 00:27:05.087
You got some questions.
It's only natural.

511
00:27:05.098 --> 00:27:08.264
And the truth is. if Irene settles...

512
00:27:08.266 --> 00:27:10.266
you'd get some money.

513
00:27:11.613 --> 00:27:14.996
But. I mean. it's not like
you guys need it. right?

514
00:27:15.507 --> 00:27:18.238
On the other hand. I did
get a look at their offer.

515
00:27:18.249 --> 00:27:20.993
I don't want to speak
out of school. but...

516
00:27:21.004 --> 00:27:22.946
it's. uh... (WHISTLES)

517
00:27:23.691 --> 00:27:27.777
But I mean. hey. everyone's
situation is different.

518
00:27:28.191 --> 00:27:30.699
Maybe Irene just doesn't need the money.

519
00:27:30.723 --> 00:27:32.622
I mean. I don't know for a fact. but...

520
00:27:32.624 --> 00:27:35.652
when you see someone
buying nice new things...

521
00:27:35.663 --> 00:27:37.827
- Like those shoes.
- like those shoes.

522
00:27:37.829 --> 00:27:39.309
Uh-huh.

523
00:27:39.831 --> 00:27:42.132
Ah. I mean. those must
have cost a pretty penny.

524
00:27:42.134 --> 00:27:43.808
I mean. if she can afford those.

525
00:27:43.819 --> 00:27:45.468
she's walkin' on easy street.

526
00:27:45.470 --> 00:27:47.886
And there's something else...

527
00:27:48.136 --> 00:27:49.917
y'know. The lawyers.

528
00:27:49.928 --> 00:27:51.644
I mean...

529
00:27:51.706 --> 00:27:54.362
that's the lawyer's
share of the settlement.

530
00:27:54.373 --> 00:27:58.065
And your share is...
boop! This much. Doo!

531
00:27:58.076 --> 00:28:03.119
If Irene holds out. the
lawyers get this much more...

532
00:28:03.121 --> 00:28:06.776
and you are gonna get this much more.

533
00:28:06.787 --> 00:28:09.070
Doesn't seem like much difference.

534
00:28:09.112 --> 00:28:11.732
I know. but that's how it works.

535
00:28:11.743 --> 00:28:13.476
And Irene knows it. too.

536
00:28:13.487 --> 00:28:15.695
I mean. the lawyers
have explained it to her.

537
00:28:15.706 --> 00:28:18.386
It's crazy. but it's all up to Irene.

538
00:28:18.417 --> 00:28:21.137
After all. she is the
Class Representative.

539
00:28:21.139 --> 00:28:23.740
Does that mean that she gets more?

540
00:28:23.742 --> 00:28:25.308
(SIGHS) No. No.

541
00:28:25.310 --> 00:28:28.519
Just means in the eyes of
the court. she's special.

542
00:28:28.530 --> 00:28:31.981
She's like your
congressman or ambassador.

543
00:28:31.983 --> 00:28:33.850
Rose: Is there anything we can do?

544
00:28:33.852 --> 00:28:37.765
No. No. You can't do anything.

545
00:28:37.776 --> 00:28:39.189
I can't do anything.

546
00:28:39.191 --> 00:28:40.605
(INHALES DEEPLY)

547
00:28:40.616 --> 00:28:42.225
Only Irene.

548
00:28:42.227 --> 00:28:43.927
(EXHALES DEEPLY)

549
00:28:43.929 --> 00:28:46.729
(BREATHES DEEPLY) She
probably knows what's best.

550
00:28:46.731 --> 00:28:49.899
I'm sure she's taking
your feelings into account.

551
00:28:49.901 --> 00:28:51.668
Hey. look at the big picture.

552
00:28:51.670 --> 00:28:54.694
Who needs money when you
got the moral high ground?

553
00:28:55.507 --> 00:28:57.106
(BREATHES DEEPLY)

554
00:29:01.084 --> 00:29:02.730
Yoo-hoo!

555
00:29:02.741 --> 00:29:04.256
Rose!

556
00:29:05.016 --> 00:29:06.498
Helen!

557
00:29:07.444 --> 00:29:09.410
Ladies?!

558
00:29:09.421 --> 00:29:11.358
Ladies!

559
00:29:17.074 --> 00:29:21.780
(JOHNNY HATES JAZZ'S "SHATTERED
DREAMS" PLAYS IN DISTANCE)

560
00:29:25.108 --> 00:29:26.603
(INSECTS CHIRPING)

561
00:29:26.605 --> 00:29:29.092
(VEHICLE APPROACHES)

562
00:29:29.825 --> 00:29:31.425
(GEARSHIFT CLICKS)

563
00:29:31.436 --> 00:29:33.710
- (DOG BARKING IN DISTANCE)
- (ENGINE SHUTS OFF)

564
00:29:33.712 --> 00:29:35.053
(VEHICLE DOOR CLOSES)

565
00:29:36.081 --> 00:29:38.678
(ENGINE REVIVING IN DISTANCE)

566
00:29:43.336 --> 00:29:47.123
(WOMAN SPEAKING SPANISH ON TELEVISION)

567
00:29:47.125 --> 00:29:48.825
(TV SHUTS OFF)

568
00:29:48.827 --> 00:29:51.494
(DOG BARKING IN DISTANCE)

569
00:29:51.496 --> 00:29:53.727
(FLOORBOARDS CREAKING)

570
00:29:53.738 --> 00:29:55.344
Ignacio?

571
00:29:55.355 --> 00:29:57.172
(CHUCKLES)

572
00:30:01.235 --> 00:30:03.006
(CHUCKLES)

573
00:30:03.008 --> 00:30:04.492
(SIGHS)

574
00:30:16.288 --> 00:30:17.876
Papa...

575
00:30:47.184 --> 00:30:49.321
Hector Salamanca.

576
00:30:52.382 --> 00:30:54.485
Salamanca.

577
00:31:01.875 --> 00:31:03.062
(SIGHS)

578
00:31:42.172 --> 00:31:44.195
(SCOFFS)

579
00:32:32.257 --> 00:32:35.292
(LIQUID POURING)

580
00:32:39.964 --> 00:32:43.332
(INSECTS CHIRPING. DOG
BARKING IN DISTANCE)

581
00:32:46.504 --> 00:32:48.081
(DOOR CLOSES)

582
00:32:48.807 --> 00:32:50.941
- (INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS)
- (SIGHS)

583
00:32:55.339 --> 00:32:56.524
(DOOR OPENS)

584
00:32:56.535 --> 00:32:59.059
Francis: Okay. and I'm still waiting
for those third-party subpoenas.

585
00:32:59.070 --> 00:33:00.590
Howard: Oh. great. Let me know. then.

586
00:33:00.601 --> 00:33:01.818
- Thanks. Francis.
- All right.

587
00:33:01.820 --> 00:33:04.520
Julie. what's up? From Chuck.

588
00:33:04.522 --> 00:33:06.522
It came via messenger...
the instructions say

589
00:33:06.524 --> 00:33:09.074
he wants you to read
it as soon as possible.

590
00:33:09.683 --> 00:33:10.985
(DOOR CLOSES)

591
00:33:10.996 --> 00:33:12.238
Mm-hmm.

592
00:33:12.785 --> 00:33:14.530
Uh. here's what I need you to do.

593
00:33:14.532 --> 00:33:18.267
Call around. Find someplace
special for the retirement party.

594
00:33:18.269 --> 00:33:20.136
Something classy. old-school.

595
00:33:20.138 --> 00:33:21.838
Uh. La Posada. maybe.

596
00:33:21.840 --> 00:33:25.149
And a band. Something jazzy. Upbeat.

597
00:33:25.160 --> 00:33:26.316
Find what's available.

598
00:33:26.327 --> 00:33:27.714
- Let's set it up.
- Okay.

599
00:33:27.726 --> 00:33:29.410
(ENVELOPE TEARING)

600
00:33:29.782 --> 00:33:31.355
(DOOR OPENS)

601
00:33:32.609 --> 00:33:34.066
(DOOR CLOSES)

602
00:33:41.695 --> 00:33:43.531
Goddamit. Chuck.

603
00:33:43.561 --> 00:33:44.898
(DOOR OPENS)

604
00:33:45.984 --> 00:33:48.109
You're suing Hamlin. Hamlin. McGill?

605
00:33:48.120 --> 00:33:49.827
Come on in. Howard.

606
00:33:50.804 --> 00:33:52.099
(DOOR SLAMS)

607
00:33:52.110 --> 00:33:53.553
(SIZZLING)

608
00:33:53.564 --> 00:33:55.210
You turned the lights on.

609
00:33:55.221 --> 00:33:58.741
I told you... I'm back to normal.

610
00:33:58.743 --> 00:34:02.223
And yes. I am suing HHM
for breach of contract.

611
00:34:02.234 --> 00:34:04.242
Do you have any idea what you're doing?

612
00:34:04.253 --> 00:34:06.015
(SIGHS) I believe I do.

613
00:34:06.026 --> 00:34:07.984
I'm calling your bluff.

614
00:34:07.986 --> 00:34:10.754
This is my firm. I built it.

615
00:34:10.765 --> 00:34:14.223
Your father was working in a
two-room office when I joined him.

616
00:34:14.225 --> 00:34:17.231
And you I tutored for the bar exam.

617
00:34:17.242 --> 00:34:18.661
You're not kicking me out.

618
00:34:18.663 --> 00:34:20.997
If you can't "trust my
judgment." as you say.

619
00:34:20.999 --> 00:34:22.331
so be it.

620
00:34:22.333 --> 00:34:25.277
but you're gonna have
to pay me for my share.

621
00:34:25.288 --> 00:34:28.337
I believe it comes to around $8 million.

622
00:34:28.339 --> 00:34:30.960
We both know the firm
doesn't have the money.

623
00:34:32.312 --> 00:34:35.246
You'd rather tear down HHM than retire?

624
00:34:35.257 --> 00:34:38.172
You think I'm trouble
now? As your partner?

625
00:34:38.183 --> 00:34:40.273
Imagine me as your enemy.

626
00:34:43.174 --> 00:34:44.694
(IMMERSION BLENDER WHIRRING)

627
00:34:44.705 --> 00:34:46.038
Chuck...

628
00:34:46.900 --> 00:34:48.424
the damage that you're going to do...

629
00:34:48.426 --> 00:34:50.416
- (WHIRRING STOPS)
- If you'd like to discuss this further.

630
00:34:50.427 --> 00:34:52.639
we can... in court.

631
00:34:52.650 --> 00:34:54.230
Until then...

632
00:34:55.080 --> 00:34:57.600
what else is there to say?

633
00:34:58.344 --> 00:35:00.811
(WHIRRING CONTINUES)

634
00:35:06.227 --> 00:35:07.693
(DOOR OPENS)

635
00:35:07.705 --> 00:35:09.374
(DOOR SLAMS)

636
00:35:09.376 --> 00:35:11.127
(WHIRRING STOPS)

637
00:35:11.138 --> 00:35:12.885
(SIZZLING)

638
00:35:13.564 --> 00:35:16.046
(SNIFFLES. CLEARS THROAT)

639
00:35:16.057 --> 00:35:18.087
(SIGHS) Blue pot. Red wine.

640
00:35:18.089 --> 00:35:19.889
Black burner.

641
00:35:19.891 --> 00:35:21.924
Blue pot. Red wine.

642
00:35:22.541 --> 00:35:25.658
Black burner. Blue pot.
Red wine. Black burner.

643
00:35:26.822 --> 00:35:28.392
(CLEARS THROAT)

644
00:35:29.267 --> 00:35:30.635
(SIGHING)

645
00:35:33.994 --> 00:35:37.657
(AIR HISSING)

646
00:35:45.012 --> 00:35:47.079
(LIQUID SLOSHING)

647
00:35:51.431 --> 00:35:52.897
(BALL TAPS)

648
00:35:57.622 --> 00:35:59.255
(LIQUID SLOSHING)

649
00:36:13.334 --> 00:36:15.674
(BALLS CLATTERING)

650
00:36:15.685 --> 00:36:17.385
Jimmy: I got hot hands.

651
00:36:17.387 --> 00:36:20.130
I got hot hands! I know
this is gonna be the one!

652
00:36:20.141 --> 00:36:22.524
B-9!

653
00:36:22.572 --> 00:36:26.998
Let's hope that biopsy comes back "B-9."

654
00:36:27.009 --> 00:36:28.591
B-9.

655
00:36:29.224 --> 00:36:30.899
(DOOR OPENS)

656
00:36:31.982 --> 00:36:34.162
Okay... what's next?

657
00:36:34.173 --> 00:36:35.506
(AIR HISSES)

658
00:36:35.517 --> 00:36:37.716
We got... I-29.

659
00:36:37.727 --> 00:36:40.107
I remember when I was 29.

660
00:36:40.118 --> 00:36:42.352
Bet you do. too.

661
00:36:42.363 --> 00:36:44.694
I-29.

662
00:36:50.380 --> 00:36:53.974
Here comes O-62.

663
00:36:54.951 --> 00:36:56.658
Oh. my God.

664
00:36:56.660 --> 00:36:59.005
Have I called 62 of
these already? (CHUCKLING)

665
00:36:59.016 --> 00:37:02.130
It feels like it. O-62.

666
00:37:03.107 --> 00:37:05.341
Here we have B-2.

667
00:37:05.352 --> 00:37:06.787
B-2.

668
00:37:06.798 --> 00:37:09.504
Well. tonight is all bingo.

669
00:37:09.506 --> 00:37:10.849
Here it comes.

670
00:37:10.860 --> 00:37:13.508
O-70. Anyone? O-70.

671
00:37:14.130 --> 00:37:16.232
All right. No takers.

672
00:37:16.243 --> 00:37:17.787
Boom!

673
00:37:18.349 --> 00:37:19.948
G-55.

674
00:37:19.950 --> 00:37:21.350
G-55.

675
00:37:21.352 --> 00:37:23.018
Oh. my God! Bingo!

676
00:37:23.020 --> 00:37:24.357
- I got bingo!
- (APPLAUSE)

677
00:37:24.368 --> 00:37:26.588
Big Paul. bring it up.

678
00:37:26.590 --> 00:37:28.260
Kelly. take a look.

679
00:37:28.271 --> 00:37:30.740
- (APPLAUSE CONTINUES)
- We may have a winner.

680
00:37:31.322 --> 00:37:34.177
Kelly. tell me... have we got it?

681
00:37:34.188 --> 00:37:35.484
We have a bingo!

682
00:37:35.495 --> 00:37:37.962
Paul. step up to the winner's circle.

683
00:37:37.973 --> 00:37:39.341
Let's hear it for him!

684
00:37:39.352 --> 00:37:41.585
Let's give him a big round of applause!

685
00:37:41.596 --> 00:37:43.863
(APPLAUSE)

686
00:37:43.874 --> 00:37:46.208
Okay. New game. new cards.

687
00:37:46.210 --> 00:37:47.709
Here they come.

688
00:37:47.711 --> 00:37:50.127
Get yourself some new cards. New cards.

689
00:37:50.138 --> 00:37:51.747
(MICROPHONE FEEDBACK)

690
00:37:51.749 --> 00:37:54.339
The helpers have them.
You can have one. two.

691
00:37:54.350 --> 00:37:56.654
You can have up to four. as you know.

692
00:37:57.052 --> 00:37:59.846
Here's a lucky blue one for you.

693
00:37:59.857 --> 00:38:03.357
All right. Take your cards
so we can start a new game.

694
00:38:03.359 --> 00:38:06.326
There you go. Add that to your stack.

695
00:38:07.459 --> 00:38:08.996
All right. Get your cards.

696
00:38:08.998 --> 00:38:11.549
Hey. Irene. you feeling lucky today?

697
00:38:11.560 --> 00:38:13.167
I-I guess so.

698
00:38:13.169 --> 00:38:15.903
(CHUCKLING) All right.
Well. here's one on me...

699
00:38:15.905 --> 00:38:17.371
just for you.

700
00:38:18.177 --> 00:38:23.271
All right. I sold my
soul for B-I-N-G-and-O!

701
00:38:23.779 --> 00:38:26.310
Let's clear the table.

702
00:38:26.321 --> 00:38:28.935
(INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS)

703
00:38:30.360 --> 00:38:31.998
(SNIFFLES)

704
00:38:45.836 --> 00:38:47.321
Load it up.

705
00:38:47.891 --> 00:38:51.104
(BALLS CLATTERING)

706
00:38:53.813 --> 00:38:55.542
Locked and loaded.

707
00:38:55.544 --> 00:38:57.180
(CABINET DOOR CLOSES)

708
00:38:57.191 --> 00:38:58.704
(SIGHS)

709
00:39:02.617 --> 00:39:04.636
Here comes a new game.

710
00:39:04.647 --> 00:39:05.880
(SWITCH CLICKS)

711
00:39:09.391 --> 00:39:11.892
First number up...

712
00:39:13.883 --> 00:39:16.488
It's N-31.

713
00:39:16.499 --> 00:39:18.039
"N" for "Nancy."

714
00:39:18.050 --> 00:39:21.263
31 for the number of times
she told me to take a hike.

715
00:39:21.274 --> 00:39:24.211
N-31.

716
00:39:26.446 --> 00:39:28.224
G-48.

717
00:39:28.235 --> 00:39:30.688
"G" for the Greatest Generation.

718
00:39:30.699 --> 00:39:33.814
48 for "Dewey Defeats Truman."

719
00:39:33.816 --> 00:39:37.349
Here's I-25... the big "I."

720
00:39:37.360 --> 00:39:38.903
I-25.

721
00:39:38.953 --> 00:39:42.823
It's B-12. like the vitamin.

722
00:39:50.876 --> 00:39:52.466
O-67!

723
00:39:52.468 --> 00:39:55.611
Anybody? I got a good
feeling about this.

724
00:39:55.622 --> 00:39:58.212
O-67!

725
00:40:00.056 --> 00:40:03.436
I- I... I think... Bingo!

726
00:40:03.447 --> 00:40:04.711
Who is that?

727
00:40:04.713 --> 00:40:06.283
Come on up.

728
00:40:07.040 --> 00:40:11.240
Irene! Irene. come on up here. dear.

729
00:40:11.251 --> 00:40:13.959
Bring it up to Kelly. Let's take a look.

730
00:40:13.970 --> 00:40:16.223
Kelly has to check your card.

731
00:40:16.225 --> 00:40:18.048
(BALLS CLATTERING)

732
00:40:18.059 --> 00:40:20.159
Here she comes.

733
00:40:24.712 --> 00:40:26.556
Could be...

734
00:40:29.204 --> 00:40:31.505
Oh. my goodness.

735
00:40:31.507 --> 00:40:35.475
It is a bingo for Irene!

736
00:40:35.477 --> 00:40:37.678
Let's hear it for Irene Landry!

737
00:40:37.680 --> 00:40:39.540
(SCATTERED APPLAUSE)

738
00:40:39.556 --> 00:40:42.744
Give it up for the big
winner. Irene Landry!

739
00:40:42.755 --> 00:40:44.384
(SCATTERED APPLAUSE CONTINUES)

740
00:40:44.386 --> 00:40:46.666
Fastest bingo of the night!

741
00:40:46.677 --> 00:40:49.156
Come on. Let's hear it for Irene.

742
00:40:49.158 --> 00:40:50.442
- Oh!
- (THUMPS)

743
00:40:51.044 --> 00:40:52.092
(CRYING)

744
00:40:52.094 --> 00:40:53.294
Irene...

745
00:40:53.305 --> 00:40:54.353
- where ya goin'?
- (DOOR OPENS)

746
00:40:54.364 --> 00:40:56.560
Hey. you know what? Take over.

747
00:40:58.106 --> 00:41:00.334
Okay. Time for a new game.

748
00:41:00.336 --> 00:41:03.220
Uh. let's get some
cards out for everyone.

749
00:41:03.231 --> 00:41:04.599
(CRYING)

750
00:41:04.610 --> 00:41:06.099
(DOOR OPENS)

751
00:41:08.755 --> 00:41:10.093
(CHUCKLING) Hey.

752
00:41:10.104 --> 00:41:12.176
What's going on? You okay?

753
00:41:12.187 --> 00:41:13.987
(CRYING)

754
00:41:14.122 --> 00:41:16.189
Aww! Don't do that.

755
00:41:16.200 --> 00:41:19.122
Your mascara's gonna run all over.

756
00:41:19.133 --> 00:41:21.353
(CRYING CONTINUES)

757
00:41:21.364 --> 00:41:23.557
Irene. come on.

758
00:41:23.559 --> 00:41:25.317
What's wrong?

759
00:41:25.728 --> 00:41:27.194
(SNIFFLES)

760
00:41:27.196 --> 00:41:29.817
They've all turned on me.

761
00:41:29.828 --> 00:41:31.138
(CRYING)

762
00:41:31.149 --> 00:41:32.749
Who has?

763
00:41:33.202 --> 00:41:34.900
My friends!

764
00:41:34.937 --> 00:41:38.111
Helen. Rose. Myrtle.

765
00:41:38.122 --> 00:41:40.439
All of them.

766
00:41:40.450 --> 00:41:42.900
What? No!

767
00:41:42.911 --> 00:41:44.919
Yes!

768
00:41:44.935 --> 00:41:46.213
(SNIFFLES)

769
00:41:46.215 --> 00:41:48.567
They're so cold.

770
00:41:49.708 --> 00:41:53.502
When I walk past them.
they stop talking.

771
00:41:53.504 --> 00:41:55.380
I-I-I hear them whispering

772
00:41:55.391 --> 00:41:58.225
when... when they think I'm not there.

773
00:41:58.227 --> 00:42:00.825
It's just so...

774
00:42:00.996 --> 00:42:02.549
- It's so cruel.
- Mnh.

775
00:42:02.560 --> 00:42:04.731
And I don't even know why.

776
00:42:05.310 --> 00:42:07.763
(SIGHS)

777
00:42:09.716 --> 00:42:12.005
I think. uh...

778
00:42:12.007 --> 00:42:14.107
maybe I do.

779
00:42:15.916 --> 00:42:17.781
- You do?
- (SIGHS)

780
00:42:19.281 --> 00:42:21.248
(SIGHS)

781
00:42:21.259 --> 00:42:23.834
Could it be the settlement?

782
00:42:23.845 --> 00:42:26.529
I mean. maybe they... (INHALES SHARPLY)

783
00:42:26.540 --> 00:42:28.912
Want the money.

784
00:42:28.923 --> 00:42:32.443
you know. to improve their lives?

785
00:42:32.454 --> 00:42:35.629
I had no idea any of them needed money.

786
00:42:35.631 --> 00:42:37.831
No one said anything to me.

787
00:42:37.833 --> 00:42:40.333
Well. maybe it's not
about the money itself.

788
00:42:40.335 --> 00:42:44.805
I mean... hello... who
wouldn't want more money?

789
00:42:44.807 --> 00:42:47.376
I mean. maybe it's the idea

790
00:42:47.387 --> 00:42:52.532
that they don't think you're
considering them. you know?

791
00:42:53.189 --> 00:42:55.315
Thinking of their needs?

792
00:42:55.317 --> 00:42:57.718
I-I-I didn't know.

793
00:42:57.720 --> 00:43:01.048
I don't want to hurt
them. They're my friends.

794
00:43:01.059 --> 00:43:02.925
(BREATHING HEAVILY)

795
00:43:03.993 --> 00:43:06.460
I wish we never even
started this lawsuit.

796
00:43:06.462 --> 00:43:09.545
I just want everything
to go back the way it was.

797
00:43:09.556 --> 00:43:11.832
(BREATHING HEAVILY)

798
00:43:12.556 --> 00:43:15.251
What should I do?

799
00:43:15.947 --> 00:43:18.486
What would you do?

800
00:43:20.642 --> 00:43:24.150
I mean. you know I'm
not a lawyer right now.

801
00:43:24.900 --> 00:43:26.680
Please?

802
00:43:28.141 --> 00:43:30.212
Should I settle?

803
00:43:31.829 --> 00:43:33.653
(SIGHS)

804
00:43:34.548 --> 00:43:36.323
Irene...

805
00:43:38.337 --> 00:43:39.730
(SIGHS)

806
00:43:39.741 --> 00:43:41.853
You listen to your heart.

807
00:43:54.007 --> 00:43:55.909
Uh. time?

808
00:43:55.911 --> 00:43:57.177
Two hours out.

809
00:43:57.179 --> 00:43:58.712
When did I say I was gonna leave?

810
00:43:58.714 --> 00:44:00.380
20 minutes ago.

811
00:44:01.117 --> 00:44:03.644
Uh. can I have some more coffee. please?

812
00:44:03.655 --> 00:44:05.468
Coming.

813
00:44:10.459 --> 00:44:13.451
Uh. I'm missing a survey
history in this one.

814
00:44:13.462 --> 00:44:15.990
- On it. Sorry about that.
- (SIGHS)

815
00:44:16.001 --> 00:44:17.537
- (COFFEE POURING)
- Not a problem.

816
00:44:17.548 --> 00:44:19.232
- (DOOR OPENS)
- Jimmy: Hey!

817
00:44:19.234 --> 00:44:21.735
Who's ready to have her life changed?

818
00:44:21.737 --> 00:44:23.270
Kim. did you hear me?

819
00:44:23.272 --> 00:44:25.338
Yep. Heard you. Life changed.

820
00:44:25.349 --> 00:44:29.142
(CHUCKLES) Stop your work.
both of you. for a sec.

821
00:44:29.144 --> 00:44:30.811
I-I got big. big news.

822
00:44:30.813 --> 00:44:32.646
Can you just tell us later. Jimmy?

823
00:44:32.648 --> 00:44:35.397
- I'm so late. it's not even funny.
- Mesa Verde can wait.

824
00:44:35.408 --> 00:44:38.251
- Look. I got Zafiro.
- It's not Mesa Verde.

825
00:44:38.253 --> 00:44:40.620
It's a new client. and if I mess
this up. it's a former client.

826
00:44:40.622 --> 00:44:42.722
I thought Mesa Verde
was your one and only.

827
00:44:42.724 --> 00:44:44.624
You know. it's go...
Ji... uh. I'm sorry.

828
00:44:44.635 --> 00:44:46.650
Jimmy. can I just explain
all this to you later? I'm...

829
00:44:46.661 --> 00:44:48.869
Sandpiper is settling.

830
00:44:49.498 --> 00:44:51.819
- What?
- (CHUCKLING) Yeah.

831
00:44:51.830 --> 00:44:53.462
For a bundle.

832
00:44:54.361 --> 00:44:56.169
But Th-they can't be settling.

833
00:44:56.171 --> 00:44:58.171
(CHUCKLING) Class actions
don't move that fast.

834
00:44:58.173 --> 00:45:00.407
Don't get bogged down in the details!

835
00:45:00.432 --> 00:45:03.150
Trust me... they're settling!

836
00:45:04.717 --> 00:45:05.983
- Wow. that...
- (BOTH CHUCKLE)

837
00:45:05.994 --> 00:45:07.762
- Yeah. Yeah!
- That's great. then.

838
00:45:07.773 --> 00:45:09.616
So. hey. let's celebrate.

839
00:45:09.618 --> 00:45:11.145
I can tell that you...

840
00:45:11.156 --> 00:45:13.453
pulled another
all-nighter here. you know?

841
00:45:13.455 --> 00:45:15.989
You... you got to stop
and smell the roses.

842
00:45:15.991 --> 00:45:18.992
Hey. who's got two
thumbs. a bottle of Zafiro.

843
00:45:18.994 --> 00:45:20.926
and 20% of the common fund?!

844
00:45:20.937 --> 00:45:22.128
- Huh?
- This guy!

845
00:45:22.130 --> 00:45:24.598
I know... you do. Uh. I
am happy for you. Jimmy.

846
00:45:24.600 --> 00:45:25.932
Be happy for us!

847
00:45:25.934 --> 00:45:28.246
This is the solution to everything.

848
00:45:28.257 --> 00:45:29.781
Okay. Francesca. could you
just put these all in my car?

849
00:45:29.792 --> 00:45:31.320
Kim.

850
00:45:31.331 --> 00:45:32.590
Yeah. Jimmy. I gotta go.

851
00:45:32.601 --> 00:45:34.496
Gimme five goddamn minutes.

852
00:45:34.507 --> 00:45:36.257
- I don't have five minutes.
- But you're already late.

853
00:45:36.268 --> 00:45:39.012
What's five more minutes?
So drive 60 instead of 55.

854
00:45:39.014 --> 00:45:40.625
- (CHUCKLING) Jimmy!
- What?

855
00:45:40.636 --> 00:45:42.135
- (DOOR OPENS)
- You're not hearing me.

856
00:45:42.146 --> 00:45:43.984
Our troubles are over! Come on!

857
00:45:43.986 --> 00:45:45.707
Jimmy. I'm leaving now.

858
00:45:45.718 --> 00:45:46.987
I'll be back in a few hours.

859
00:45:46.998 --> 00:45:48.187
Think of all the things
you want to say to me.

860
00:45:48.198 --> 00:45:49.814
and just say them to me later. okay?

861
00:45:49.825 --> 00:45:51.203
Bye.

862
00:45:51.214 --> 00:45:52.575
(DOOR CLOSES)

863
00:45:57.832 --> 00:45:59.379
(DOOR OPENS)

864
00:46:01.434 --> 00:46:02.739
(DOOR CLOSES)

865
00:46:02.750 --> 00:46:04.854
You. Shots.

866
00:46:04.888 --> 00:46:07.272
- Uh. I...
- Shots.

867
00:46:07.283 --> 00:46:09.149
We're celebrating.

868
00:46:15.123 --> 00:46:17.317
- Cheers.
- (GLASSES CLINK)

869
00:46:18.686 --> 00:46:20.573
(SLURPS)

870
00:46:20.584 --> 00:46:21.865
Smooth.

871
00:46:21.876 --> 00:46:23.523
(EXHALES SHARPLY)

872
00:46:23.525 --> 00:46:25.058
(TAPPING COUNTER)

873
00:46:25.060 --> 00:46:26.475
Yeah.

874
00:46:31.029 --> 00:46:35.001
Under the terms we're offering.
you get a substantial payment

875
00:46:35.003 --> 00:46:38.292
without any impact to your property
via drilling and extraction.

876
00:46:38.303 --> 00:46:39.673
And rather than waiting years to close.

877
00:46:39.675 --> 00:46:43.354
Mr. Gatwood is offering cash
on the barrel. right now.

878
00:46:43.365 --> 00:46:46.456
Given the cost of overhead. liabilities.

879
00:46:46.467 --> 00:46:48.748
and other burdens Mr. Gatwood assumes.

880
00:46:48.750 --> 00:46:51.311
we believe this offer is more than fair.

881
00:46:51.322 --> 00:46:52.918
We believe...

882
00:46:53.405 --> 00:46:56.920
we believe this offer is more than fair.

883
00:47:10.205 --> 00:47:11.859
(GASPS)

884
00:47:11.870 --> 00:47:15.398
(AIR RUSHING)

885
00:47:16.015 --> 00:47:19.406
(BREATHING HEAVILY)

886
00:47:25.305 --> 00:47:27.625
(DOOR CREAKS)

887
00:47:33.729 --> 00:47:37.063
(WHIMPERS)

888
00:47:38.273 --> 00:47:39.958
Aah!

889
00:47:39.969 --> 00:47:44.371
(BREATHING SHAKILY)

890
00:48:01.356 --> 00:48:04.724
(WIND WHISTLING)

